race.comment: SINE QUA NON (1) was only 0.3 lengths from the winner in second last time out in a small field over 1106m at this track (Turf) at the first run of the campaign. Will be fitter for that run, expected to go close again. OY GEVALD (14) started at $9.14 last time and ran below expectations, finishing 11th and beaten 10 lengths at Kentucky (Turf) over 1609m. Finds a suitable assignment and can find winning form. DEFENDING ALBERT (10) is in top form with two wins on end, the most recent an effortless 6 lengths victory over 1207m at Fairmount Park (Dirt) a month ago. Has good early toe so he should be handy in the run. Should be involved in the finish. DR. PERRY (6) is racing well and is close to a win, the latest effort a solid third at Canterbury Park (Turf) over 1006m. Has his share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. Something for the Multiples: DR. PERRY (6) MARTINI MAN (5)
